<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a12098c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6555"><num value="6555">§ 6555.</num><heading> Relation to other laws</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The authority provided to each Secretary under this subchapter is supplemental to, and not in lieu of, any authority provided to the Secretaries under any other law.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a12098d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/108/148/tIV/s405">Pub. L. 108–148, title IV, § 405</ref>, <date date="2003-12-03">Dec. 3, 2003</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/117/1911">117 Stat. 1911</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
